&lt;h3&gt;(Chinese characters）&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;pp24 - 25 of the textbook lists some of the basic Chinese characters and the derivations evolved from them that appear in the current lesson. Please study them carefully and learn to write them and memorize them. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(230,126,34);"&gt;(Grammar)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;(Sentences with an adjectival predicate)&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adjectives in Chinese can function directly as predicates. This kind of sentences is called a sentence with an adjectival predicte. Adjectives in this kind of sentence can be modified by adverbs suchas. The negative form of sentences with an adjectival predicate is generated by placing the negative adverb before the adjective that functions as the predicate. For example: . &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(230,126,34);"&gt;Note&lt;/span&gt; : Adverbs such as must be placed before the adjective they modify.&lt;/p&gt;
